The paper discusses the representation of symbolic knowledge in connectionist networks, which is a topic closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of restricted Boltzmann machines (RBMs) also suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of logical inference rules, which is a topic in computational logic (cs.CL) and the evaluation of the proposed method on real datasets suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
